exhibition_title: From Dürer to Cassatt: Five Centuries of Master Prints from the Jones Collection
exhibition_description:
This exhibition will showcase the remarkable depth of the Herschel V. Jones Collection, the seminal gift at the core of The Minneapolis Institute of Arts print holdings. The exhibition will consist of seventy-five to eighty-five engravings, lithographs and woodcuts. Including will be dozens of rarely or never-seen masterpieces representing five centuries of printmaking, arranged comprehensively by school and genre. The exhibition will continue from US Bank Gallery into the Old Masters, 18th and 19th C permanent collection galleries on the museum’s third floor.
A fully illustrated catalogue accompanies the exhibition.
